218
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:26,059
Act on last resort?

219
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:28,760
You decided to ask him directly, right?

220
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:34,159
About how to make sandwich from Amuro.

221
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:35,160
What?

222
00:15:35,161 --> 00:15:36,660
Is that right?

223
00:15:37,660 --> 00:15:41,159
I recently heard that the sandwiches here are cheap and good so...

224
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:42,960
I came to try some.

225
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,760
I was shocked...

226
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,259
by how delicious they were!

227
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,560
The ham sandwich in particular is superb.

228
00:15:57,860 --> 00:16:01,159
So, I got to thinking I wanted to make sandwiches

229
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,860
that tasted just as good.

230
00:16:03,660 --> 00:16:06,259
But no matter how much I watched how you made it,

231
00:16:06,260 --> 00:16:07,960
